    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available is a driver-focused 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six power plant. This high-revving mill utilizes individual throttle bodies and a dual-VANOS variable valve timing system, both of which have been meticulously serviced to ensure optimal volumetric efficiency. Power is routed through a traditional 6-speed longitudinal manual gearbox to a factory limited-slip differential, providing exceptional mechanical grip and exit speeds. The chassis has been enhanced with Bilstein B16 coil-overs and the rear subframe\u2014a known weak point\u2014has been professionally reinforced to maintain structural rigidity under high lateral loads. While showing minor aesthetic patina reflective of its age, the car remains a mechanically sound example of BMW\u2019s 'Ultimate Driving Machine' era, offering a tactile, analog steering response and a balanced 50/50 weight distribution.",
